name: Jetpack Janitor
oracle_text: Alpha strike (This creature has first strike as long as it's blocking or being blocked by a creature that comes after it alphabetically.)
flavor_text: "'Carol, blast those aliens.' 'Carol, transport these concessions.' No one cares that today is my birthday."

name: Impounding Lot-Bot
oracle_text: When Impounding Lot-Bot enters the battlefield, you may say "INCARCERATE!" in a robot voice. If you do, exile another target artifact or enchantment until Impounding Lot-Bot leaves the battlefield.
flavor_text: Not all tickets can be exchanged for prizes.

name: Pin Collection
Park Re-Entry
oracle_text: Return up to two target creature cards that each have a hat and/or mana value 3 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor_text:
"Control to Truss. Chief, the entry scan software is reading babies as hot dogs. Again."
—Glaxxar, engineering assistant

name: Park Bleater
oracle_text:
Whenever another creature you own enters the battlefield, you get {TIX}.
{W}, {T}: You may put a sticker on a creature you own that entered the battlefield this turn.
flavor_text: Once he stopped eating tickets, Bixby was a model employee.

name: Now You See Me . . .
oracle_text: Exile target creature you control, then return it to the battlefield under its owner's control with X +1/+1 counters on it, where X is the number of mirrors on walls you can see from your seat.
flavor_text: With enough showmanship, even mundane items like playing cards or molecular teleports can produced a mesmerizing spectacle.

name: T.A.P.P.E.R.
oracle_text: {T}, Tap an untapped creature you control that has a hat: Tap target creature.
flavor_text:
"'Technologically-Advanced People-Pleasing Entertainment Robot', eh? Nice hat. Would be a shame if something happened to it."
—"Brims" Barone, midway mobster

name: Sword-Swallowing Seraph
oracle_text:
Flying, vigilance
When Sword-Swallowing Seraph enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
{1}{W}, {T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on another target creature with a name sticker on it. Activate only as a sorcery.

name: Starlight Spectacular
oracle_text: Parade! — At the beginning of combat on your turn, choose creatures you control one at a time until each creature you control has been chosen. Each of those creatures gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each creature chosen before it. (Places everyone! The first creature in line gets +0/+0.)

name: Solaflora, Intergalactic Icon
oracle_text:
Auras and Equipment you control attached to Solaflora, Intergalactic Icon affect other creatures you control as though those Auras and Equipment were attached to them.
Counters and stickers on Solaflora affect other creatures you control as though those counters and stickers were on them.

name: Sanguine Sipper
oracle_text: Sanguine Sipper has lifelink as long as you control a stickered permanent.
flavor_text: The midway offers every flavor under the sun, even to guests who need to stay out of it.

name: Ride Guide
oracle_text: When Ride Guide enters the battlefield, open an attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: "When riding Erebo's Whip, remember to keep your arms, legs, and any strange flailing appendages inside the vehicle at all times."

name: Trapeze Artist
oracle_text:
Flying
Trapeze Artist enters the battlefield by being flipped from a height of at least one foot (about 0.3 meters). If it lands face down or didn't turn over completely at least once during the flip, return it to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: Heinrich catches the trapeze only about half the time, but he looks so good falling.

name: Bag Check
oracle_text: Counter target spell, then as a person outside the game if that spell looks dangerous to them. If they say yes, draw a card, then discard a card.
flavor_text: "As long as there's no outside food, you're good to go."

name: Baaallerina
oracle_text:
Flying
When Baaallerina enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
{2}{U}: Another target creature with a name sticker on it gains flying until end of turn.
flavor_text: Cute as a mutton.

name: Astroquarium
oracle_text:
When Astroquarium enters the battlefield, you may put an art sticker on it.
{1}, {T}: Until end of turn, target creature becomes a blue Shark with base power and toughness 4/4. If the cracks in Astroquarium's art are completely covered, that creature becomes a blue Octopus with base power and toughness 8/8 instead. Activate only as a sorcery.

name: Decisions, Decisions
oracle_text: Reveal the top three cards of your library, then choose a consonant. (Y counts.) Put each card that has the chosen letter in the first word of its name from among them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Croakid Amphibonaut
oracle_text: Croakid Amphibonaut has flying as long as you control a stickered permanent.
flavor_text:
"I designed the Astrotorium's jetpacks to be lightweight and inexpensive. Nobody mentioned reliable."
—Truss, chief engineer

name: Command Performance
oracle_text:
Choose two —
• Open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
• Roll to visit your Attractions.
• You get {TIX}{TIX}.
• You may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.

name: Boing!
oracle_text: Return target creature to its owner's hand, then roll a six-sided die. If the result is 3 or less, scry a number of cards equal to the result.
flavor_text: Sometimes the Astrotorium's stunts look dangerous because they absolutely are.

name: Blufferfish
oracle_text: {3}{U}: An opponent tells you a statement about themselves and secretly notes whether it's true or not. You guess which it is. If you guessed correctly, Blufferfish gets +2/+0 and can't be blocked this turn.
flavor_text: Lying to a fish is such an unthinkable act, most planets don't even have a law against it.

name: Bamboozling Beeble
oracle_text:
Protection from Robots
{1}, {T}: The next tie target player would roll one or more dice this turn, instead they roll that many dice plus one and you choose one to those rolls to ignore.
flavor_text: Myra bought beetles because they were cheaper than rubber ducks. Now the infestation is her largest expense.

name: How Is This a Par Three?!
oracle_text: Whenever you cast a spell, you may have target player mill X cards, where X is the number of words in that spell's name.
flavor_text: Against the infinite backdrop of space, isn't all golf miniature?

name: Glitterflitter
oracle_text:
Flying
When Glitterflitter enters the battlefield, you get {TIX}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
flavor_text: There are no small parts, only small performers.

name: Focused Funambulist
oracle_text:
Flash
As Focused Funambulist enters the battlefield, you may put an art sticker on the empty side of the balancing pole. When you do, ask a person outside the game "Does this look balanced?" If they say yes, you may tap or untap target creature.

name: Fluros of Myra's Marvels
oracle_text:
As Fluros of Myra's Marvels enters the battlefield, choose a number greater than 0.
Whenever you cast a spell with power, toughness, or loyalty equal to the chosen number, target artifact or creature becomes an artifact creature with base power and toughness X/X, where X is the chosen number.
Partner

name: Exchange of Words
oracle_text: When Exchange of Words enters the battlefield, choose two target creatures. For as long as Exchange of Words remains on the battlefield, exchange the text boxes of those creatures.
flavor_text: Before criticizing, walk a mile *(about 1.6 kilometers)* in their head. That way, when you do, you're a mile away and you have their head.

name: Plate Spinning
oracle_text: Whenever you cast a spell, copy it and you may choose new targets for the copy. Then balance a card from outside the game on one of your fingertips. When that card falls or touches another card, sacrifice Plate Spinning.
flavor_text: For extra style points, spin them.

name: Octo Opus
oracle_text:
When Octo Opus enters the battlefield, create a 4/4 blue Octopus Performer token named Contortionist with "At the beginning of your upkeep, you may fold this token in half." (It becomes 2/2, then 1/1, ½/½, and so on.)
Sacrifice Octo Opus: Draw a card and an additional card for each of Contortionist's folds.

name: Motion Sickness
oracle_text:
Enchant creature
When Motion Sickness enters the battlefield, tap enchanted creature.
Enchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.
Whenever you visit an Attraction, you may attach Motion Sickness to target tapped creature.

name: Mobile Clone
oracle_text: Using a mobile device, take a picture of target creature. That device enters the battlefield as a token that's a photocopy of the pictured creature. (Photocopies include Auras, Equipment, counters, and stickers in the shot. Don't touch other people's phones without permission and be careful if you do.)

name: Make a _____ Splash
oracle_text:
Flash
When this enchantment enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on it.
Whenever you put a sticker on this enchantment, tap up to X target creatures, where X is the number of u's in name stickers on this enchantment.
flavor_text: The largest dunk tank in forty-seven galaxies.

name: Prize Wall
oracle_text:
Defender
{U}, {T}: You get {TIX}.
{4}{U}, {T}: You may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Activate only as a sorcery.
flavor_text:
"That bear's been there since the Astrotorium opened. I've seen it move."
—Ernst, deep fry cook

name: Vedalken Squirrel-Whacker
oracle_text:
As Vedalken Squirrel-Whacker enters the battlefield, roll a six-sided die twice. Its base power becomes the first result and its base toughness becomes the second result.
If you would roll one or more six-sided dice, instead roll them and you may exchange one result with Vedalken Squirrel-Whacker's base power or base toughness.

name: Unlawful Entry
oracle_text:
Target creature gets +1/+0 and gains flying until end of turn.
Whenever you put an art sticker on a creature, you may return Unlawful Entry from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor_text:
"Glaxxar, Security Bot 254 has wandered off. After lunch, throw on a spacesuit and go find it."
—Truss, chief engineer.

name: _____ _____ _____ Trespasser
oracle_text:
When this creature enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on it.
{3}{U}: This creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn for each name sticker on it. It can't be blocked this turn.
flavor_text: "All you gotta do is walk with purpose. And run with purpose. And clear a five-foot gate with purpose."

name: Treacherous Trapezist
oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever you cast an alliterative spell, scry 2. (Anything with two or more capitalized words in its name that begin with the same letter is alliterative.)
Other alliterative creatures you control have flying.

name: Seasoned Buttoneer
oracle_text: When Seasoned Buttoneer enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: Everyone comments on the buttons, but few appreciate the pedals.

name: Attempted Murder
oracle_text: Choose target creature. Roll X six-sided dice. For each even result, put two -1/-1 counters on that creature. For each odd result, create a 1/2 blue Bird creature token with flying named Storm Crow.
flavor_text: Squawks was quick to establish the social pecking order.

name: Animate Graveyard
oracle_text:
Enchant your graveyard
Enchanted graveyard is a creature on the battlefield with base power and toughness each equal to the number of cards in it. It has the text boxes of all creature cards in it. It's still a graveyard.
If enchanted graveyard would leave the battlefield, instead exile Animate Graveyard.

name: Carnival Carnivore
oracle_text:
Deathtouch
When Carnival Carnivore enters the battlefield, you get {TIX}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
flavor_text: Somehow only the third-most dangerous ride in the park.

name: Black Hole
oracle_text: Destroy target creature and up to X other target creatures, where X is the number of Attractions you've visited this turn.
flavor_text:
"Code Dark Donut! Code Dark Donut! All available fun specialists, please report to the Roil Coaster immediately!"
—Truss, chief engineer

name: Discourtesy Clerk
oracle_text:
When Discourtesy Clerk enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
At the beginning of your end step, if you control three or more Attractions, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor_text: Myra doesn't pay the vampires to smile—but only because guests found it off-putting.

name: Deadbeat Attendant
oracle_text: When Deadbeat Attendant enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: Some people will hire anyone with a pulse. Myra isn't that picky.

name: Haberthrasher
oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Whenever another creature that has a hat enters the battlefield under your control or a hat sticker is put on a creature you control, each opponent loses 1 life.
flavor_text: "Brims" Barone's enforcers are always dressed to kill.

name: Exit Through the Grift Shop
oracle_text: Yell "Who wants a souvenir?" and announce the name of a nonland card in your graveyard. Each player in an Un-game who can hear you may bid life. You start the bidding at 0. The high bidder loses life equal to the high bid. They copy the card and may cast the copy without paying its mana cost. If you didn't win the bid, you gain life equal to the high bid and create that many Treasure tokens.

name: Down for Repairs
oracle_text: Target opponent reveals their hand. You choose a nonland card from it. That player discards that card. Destroy up to one Attraction that player controls. (It's put into their junkyard.)
flavor_text: Safety twelfth.

name: Dissatisfied Customer
oracle_text:
Flying, haste
When Dissatisfied Customer enters the battlefield, roll a six-sided die. If the result is 3 or less, you lose that much life.
flavor_text: The mirrors weren't fun for everyone.

name: Disemvowel
oracle_text: Destroy target creature. That creature's controller loses 1 life for each unique vowel in the creature's name. (The vowels are A, E, I, O, U, and Y.)
flavor_text: Without vowels, no one can hear you scream.

name: Questionable Cuisine
oracle_text: Return up to two target creature cards from your graveyard to your hand. Create a Food token for each trash can you can see from your seat. (It's an artifact with "{2}, {T}, Sacrifice this artifact: You gain 3 life.")
flavor_text: May contain soy. May contain a deep void, chillingly hoarse and howling without voice. May contain gluten.
